{
  "texts": [
    "Schrag et al.",
    "reported an estimated VE of 86% (95% CI 28-97) against hospitalization in the Omicron period from 7 to 119 days after the receipt of a booster dose.",
    "This suggests a high level of protection during this period.",
    "However, the booster dose did not provide a statistically significant protective effect beyond 120 days before virologically confirmed SARS-CoV-2 or hospitalization [59] (Figs.",
    "S18 and S19 of the ESM).The pattern was similar for symptomatic COVID-19 by type of vaccine with VE of 78% (95% CI 21-94) for mRNA, 39% (95% CI for inactivated virus, and 25% (95% CI 0-100) for viral vector regardless the SARS-CoV-2 variant dominance."
  ]
}